From 0e8b2b46fac59b1aa6dbf42dcf3a5d6e24d5187e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESTI Contributors <esti@example.local>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 07:04:08 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] Dashboard redesign: brief-aligned hierarchy with
 utilization + ASPRF tiles

Restructures the dashboard to follow the AOMS brief's information architecture
(Global KPI Bar -> Action Center -> Financial Health -> Project Health ->
Client Intelligence -> Team Intelligence -> Revision/Technical Intelligence ->
Activity Feed):

- Global KPI Bar expanded to the brief's six KPIs: Ready to bill, Outstanding
  collections, Overdue 30d+, Active projects, Team utilization (new), Revision risk
- New dashboard.utilization query: 30-day timesheet hours vs headcount capacity
  (~22 days x 8h) plus billable rate
- Action Center expanded from 3 to the brief's 5 categories: overdue collections,
  approvals pending, ready to bill (with estimated value), high-risk projects,
  team capacity alerts
- Project Health is now a per-project board (brief's project-card structure):
  ref/title link, current phase, ProgressBar progress %, signal tags, health tag;
  projectHealth query enriched with current_phase + progress_pct
- Client Intelligence radar chart replaced with a readable signals table:
  projects, outstanding, oldest invoice age, approval lag, revisions, risk tag
- Team Intelligence now shows ASPRF member cards (performance score, band tag,
  capacity tag, open/overdue/points) joining aspRf.teamScores with capacity signals
- Removed task-minutiae charts from the dashboard (type treemap, daily task
  gauges, workload heatmap) - workload detail lives in the Work module
- Welcome line no longer doubles the "Ar." prefix when the name already has one

Co-Authored-By: Codex Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
